rough a critical, introduced, translated and commented edition of his sum of legal theory entitled Nukat al-Maḥṣūl fī ʿilm uṣūl, this present work shows how the legal thought of the Qāḍī is articulated between language and theology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAsharites. 0aIslamic lawxInterpretation and constructionvEarly works to 1800. 0aMalikitesvEarly works to 1800. 4aGeneral. 4aIslam. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Islam / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2z978311117804208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z97831110241270 cprintz978146324384540uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324385240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463243852423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463243852/original  a978-3-11-102412-7  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-117804-2  DG Plus PP Package 2023 Part 2b2023  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023